Re: checkpointing the block chain

Bitcointalk

2010-08-16 20:20:53 UTC - [11]Original Post

   There is no way for the software to automatically know if one chain is
   better than another except by the greatest proof-of-work.  In the
   design it was necessary for it to switch to a longer chain no matter
   how far back it has to go.
   The only exception to that is the manual checkpoints Iʼve added.  If it
   werenʼt for those, it would be able to reorg all the way back to the
   first block.
